<seg id=1> Gu Yongjiang said that mainland economic development provided Hong Kong with five chances. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Gu Yongjiang said that mainland economic development provided Hong Kong with five chances. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> It's advantageous to the long-term prosperity and stability of Hong Kong. </seg>
<seg id=4> The economic development in Hong Kong would benefit from the long-term, stable economic development in mainland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> It provided Hong Kong with more business chances. </seg>
<seg id=6> With the development of service trades and open policy in mainland such as trade, finance, retail, etc., service trades in Hong Kong would gain further development. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> It's advantageous to Hong Kong's position as the center of trade and shipping. </seg>
<seg id=8> By 2010, the total export value in mainland will be expected up to US$800 billion. There's no doubt that it will increase the need of transit trade and transport from Hong Kong, which will be advantageous to Hong Kong's position as the center of trade and shipping. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> It will promote the development of financial market in Hong Kong. </seg>
<seg id=10> With the reform of state-owned enterprises in depth, more and more stock companies would open abroad, and Hong Kong will be the first choice. </seg>
<seg id=11> This will enlarge the scope of Hong Kong stock, improve stock structure, and push forward bond market in Hong Kong. Therefore, more and more Chinese funds will appear in Hong Kong, which will enhance Hong Kong's position as the center of international finance. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> It's advantageous to improving the international competition ability of Hong Kong. </seg>
<seg id=13> Economic co-operation and combination of superiority between mainland and Hong Kong will improve the international competition ability of Hong Kong. </seg>
</p>
